# Database migrations (Flyway)

## Location

- SQL migrations live under **`backend/src/main/resources/migration/`** (Flyway: `spring.flyway.locations: classpath:migration` in `application.yml`).
- See **`migration/README.md`** in that folder for the current next-version note and team rules.

## Naming

- Pattern: **`V{version}__{description}.sql`** (e.g. `V25__add_column_to_room.sql`).
- Use the **next version number** after the highest existing `V*.sql` in that folder (update `README.md` when you add a migration if it documents the latest number).
- Description: lowercase, words separated by underscores, short and specific.

## Content

- Make migrations **idempotent only if** the project already uses that pattern; otherwise prefer straightforward forward-only DDL/DML consistent with existing scripts.
- Keep changes scoped to one logical change per file when possible.
